VClearly, the global vote is not a stand-alone project.
p209
aVIt's not just there on its own.
p210
aVIt has some background.
p211
aVIt's part of a project which I launched back in 2014,
p212
aVwhich I call the Good Country.
p213
aVThe idea of the Good Country is basically very simple.
p214
aVIt's my simple diagnosis of what's wrong with the world
p215
aVand how we can fix it.
p216
aVWhat's wrong with the world I've already hinted at.
p217
aVBasically, we face an enormous and growing number
p218
aVof gigantic, existential global challenges:
p219
aVclimate change, human rights abuses,
p220
aVmass migration, terrorism, economic chaos, weapons proliferation.
p221
aVAll of these problems which threaten to wipe us out
p222
aVare by their very nature globalized problems.
p223
aVNo individual country has the capability of tackling them on its own.
p224
aa(lp225
VAnd so very obviously
p226
aVwe have to cooperate and we have to collaborate as nations
p227
aVif we're going to solve these problems.
p228
aVIt's so obvious, and yet we don't.
p229
aVWe don't do it nearly often enough.
p230
aVMost of the time, countries still persist in behaving
p231
aVas if they were warring, selfish tribes battling against each other,
p232
aVmuch as they have done since the nation-state was invented
p233
aVhundreds of years ago.
p234
aVAnd this has got to change.
p235
aVThis is not a change in political systems or a change in ideology.
p236
aVThis is a change in culture.
p237
aa(lp238
VWe, all of us, have to understand
p239
aVthat thinking inwards is not the solution to the world's problems.
p240
aVWe have to learn how to cooperate and collaborate a great deal more
p241
aVand compete just a tiny bit less.
p242
aVOtherwise things are going to carry on getting bad
p243
aVand they're going to get much worse, much sooner than we anticipate.
p244
aVThis change will only happen
p245
aVif we ordinary people
p246
aVtell our politicians that things have changed.
p247
aVWe have to tell them that the culture has changed.
p248
aVWe have to tell them that they've got a new mandate.
p249
aVThe old mandate was very simple and very single:
p250
aVif you're in a position of power or authority,
p251
aVyou're responsible for your own people and your own tiny slice of territory,
p252
aVand that's it.
p253
aVAnd if in order to do the best thing for your own people,
p254
aVyou screw over everybody else on the planet, that's even better.
p255
aVThat's considered to be a bit macho.
p256
aVToday, I think everybody in a position of power and responsibility
p257
aVhas got a dual mandate,
p258
aVwhich says if you're in a position of power and responsibility,
p259
aVyou're responsible for your own people
p260
aVand for every single man, woman, child and animal on the planet.
p261
aVYou're responsible for your own slice of territory
p262
aVand for every single square mile of the earth's surface
p263
aVand the atmosphere above it.
p264
aVAnd if you don't like that responsibility, you should not be in power.
p265
aVThat for me is the rule of the modern age,
p266
aVand that's the message that we've got to get across to our politicians,
p267
aVand show them that that's the way things are done these days.
p268
aVOtherwise, we're all screwed.
